(11309, 'sulfasalazine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions: Reduced absorption of folic acid and digoxin have been reported when those agents were administered concomitantly with sulfasalazine.', 'DailyMed'),
(11309, 'sulfamethoxazole and trimethoprim', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Because sulfamethoxazole and trimethoprim may interfere with folic acid metabolism, sulfamethoxazole and trimethoprim should be used during pregnancy only if the potential benefit justifies the potential risk to the fetus. Hematological changes indicative of folic acid deficiency may occur in elderly patients.', 'DailyMed'),
